<h4 id="high-concept">High Concept</h4>

<p><img src="/assets/img/image14.png" alt="image" title="image" />
The original Burnout gameâ€™s X Statement
is:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>â€œHigh-Speed, High-Octane, High-Impact Actionâ€</p>
</blockquote>

<p>The use of the word â€œImpactâ€ has 2 meanings here, firstly it means
crashing, secondly it refers to the effect it has on you.</p>

<h4 id="risk--reward-styleclear-both">Risk = Reward {style=â€clear: both;â€}</h4>

<p><img src="/assets/img/image15.png" alt="image" title="image" /></p>

<p>What takes Burnout beyond a regular car driving game is the element of
â€œRisk = Rewardâ€. The more dangerous you drive, the more risks you take
the greater the reward. This goes around in a loop as the Reward is
boost, which enables you to go faster and take more Risks, which
generates more Boost.</p>

<h4 id="paradise-city-styleclear-both">Paradise City {style=â€clear: both;â€}</h4>

<p><img src="/assets/img/image16.png" alt="image" title="image" /></p>

<p>â€œExplore over 250 miles of open road, discovering jumps, stunts and
